.. _syscheck:

.. OS:intopt:: syscheck.sleep

    ``ospatrol-syscheckd`` uses this setting to determine how long to sleep after reading ``syscheck.sleep_after`` 
    number of files. By default ``ospatrol-syscheckd`` sleeps for 2 seconds after checking 15 files.

    **Default:** 2

.. OS:intopt:: syscheck.sleep_after

    ``ospatrol-syscheckd`` reads this many files before sleeping for ``syscheck.sleep`` seconds.

    **Default:** 15
